org.xmlcml.cml.tools
Class AtomMatcher

java.lang.Object
  org.xmlcml.cml.tools.AbstractTool
      org.xmlcml.cml.tools.AtomMatcher
All Implemented Interfaces:
CMLConstants, EuclidConstants
public class AtomMatcher
extends AbstractTool

manages information for matching atoms. excludeElementTypes is list of elementTypes (CML) to exclude (empty => none) includeElementTypes is list of elementTypes (CML) to include (empty => all) include takes precedence over exclude useCharge determines whether formal atom charge is used useLabel determines whether atom label is used maximumAtomTreeLevel maximum level to explore trees to atomMatchStrategy MapTool.MATCH_MORGAN, etc. atomSetExpansionStrategy MapTool.MATCH_GEOM, etc.

public CMLMap mapAtomSets(CMLAtomSet atomSet0,
                          CMLAtomSet atomSet1)
                   throws CMLException
map two atomSets returns ordered list of equivalence classes. if several atoms in class uses atomSet Map may not be as large as atomSet if there are equivalence classes does not annotate links currently has two methods, Morgan and UniqueAtomLabels if the atomSets are of different lengths returns null if the Morgan fails, returns null

Parameters:
atomSet0 -
atomSet1 -
Returns:
map or null if molecules of different length.
Throws:
CMLException - null owner document, null atomSets, atom sets different sizes, bad Morgan

getMoleculeMatch

public CMLMap[][] getMoleculeMatch(java.util.List<CMLMolecule> molecule0,
                                   java.util.List<CMLMolecule> molecule1)
                            throws CMLException
matches molecules pairwise from two arrays. Heuristics currently being worked out. at present only matches molecules of equal size. each match returns a CMLMap in the matrix cell, else null. matches can be partial. array may have null elements (this is a way of deleting molecules from the problem) any match with null element gives a null CMLMap

Parameters:
molecule0 - first array of molecules
molecule1 - other array (could be a different length)
Returns:
rectangular array of maps (row = molecule0, cols=molecule1)
Throws:
CMLException - problems in molecule atom-atom matching

splitAndProcessAtomSets

public void splitAndProcessAtomSets(CMLMap map,
                                    CMLAtomSet fromAtomSet,
                                    CMLAtomSet toAtomSet)
split links containing sets of atoms into individual links. iterates through all links containing toSet and fromSet for each generates to and from atomSets. Uses atomMatchStrategy to compare and link them. if successful removes original link and adds atomSet.size() new ones some strategies may abort if sets are unequal. Currently no warning if geometrical manipulation, saves coordinates and then reapplies

Parameters:
map - context for from links
fromAtomSet - atomSet context for from links
toAtomSet - atomSet context for to links

moveReactantProductToSpectator

public void moveReactantProductToSpectator(CMLReaction reaction)
                                    throws CMLException
moves the molecule children from a reactant+product pair into a spectator. the molecules are identified by labelRefs in the spectator, e.g. "Gly23". the connection tables in the molecules are expected to be identical but might vary if hydrogen decoration was variable. The coordinates are matched, so an atomMatcher is necessary

Parameters:
reaction -
Throws:
CMLException
